<h1>ICS 269, Fall 1996: Theory Seminar</h1>

<hr>
<h2>25 Oct 1996:<br>
Polynomial Time Approximation Schemes for Euclidean TSP and Other
Geometric Problems<br>
Joseph Wang, ICS, UC Irvine</h2>

<p>Arora presents a polynomial time approximation scheme for
Euclidean TSP in <b>R</b><sup>2</sup> that finds a
(1+epsilon)-approximation tour in time <i>
n</i><sup>O(1/epsilon)</sup>. The scheme can be extended to higher
dimensions and other Euclidean problems in which the objective
function is a sum of edge lengths.</p>

<p>(From a <a href="http://www.umiacs.umd.edu/events/FOCS96/">FOCS
'96</a> <a href=
"file://ftp.cs.princeton.edu/pub/people/arora/tsp.ps">paper</a> by
<a href="http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~arora/">Sanjeev
Arora</a>)</p>
</body>
